      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "re: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/24024#issuecomment-1009754073\r\n\r\n> cs_main is a _validation_ lock. It has nothing to do with writing or reading blocks from disk (other than being historically used for that). Ideally nothing in blockman depends on cs_main.\r\n\r\nThat's a good point. It is important to have some lock guarding things like `m_block_index` but it it doesn't need to be `cs_main` and maybe ideally it would be a more narrow lock. It looks like there is more discussion about this at https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/22932#discussion_r710934432",
